  • Classes in net.opentsdb.core used by net.opentsdb.core 
    Class and Description
    AggregationIterator
    Iterator that aggregates multiple spans or time series data and does linear interpolation (lerp) for missing data points.
    Aggregator
    A function capable of aggregating multiple DataPoints together.
    Aggregator.Doubles
    A sequence of doubles.
    Aggregator.Longs
    A sequence of longs.
    Aggregators.Interpolation
    Different interpolation methods
    DataPoint
    Represents a single data point.
    DataPoints
    Represents a read-only sequence of continuous data points.
    Downsampler
    Iterator that downsamples data points using an Aggregator.
    Downsampler.ValuesInInterval
    Iterates source values for an interval.
    DownsamplingSpecification
    Representation of a downsampling specification in a TSDB query.
    FillPolicy
    Specification of how to deal with missing intervals when downsampling.
    Histogram 
    HistogramAggregation
    Aggregator functions for histogram data points.
    HistogramAggregationIterator
    This is where the real business of @{link HistogramSpanGroup}.
    HistogramCodecManager
    Manages the histogram codecs loaded by default or as plugins.
    HistogramDataPoint
    Represents a single histogram data point, e.g.
    HistogramDataPoint.HistogramBucket 
    HistogramDataPoint.HistogramBucket.BucketType 
    HistogramDataPointCodec
    Responsible for encoding or decoding HistogramDataPoints to and from byte arrays.
    HistogramDataPoints
    A clone of the DataPoints interface except for handling histograms.
    HistogramSeekableView
    A clone of the DataPoints seekable view but for histograms.
    HistogramSpan
    Represents a read-only sequence of continuous histogram data points.
    iHistogramRowSeq
    Clone of the iRowSeq interface but for histograms.
    iHistogramRowSeq.Iterator
    An interface for an iterator that all row sequences must implement.
    IncomingDataPoint
    Bridging class that stores a normalized data point parsed from the "put" RPC methods and gets it ready for storage.
    Internal.Cell
    Represents a single data point in a row.
    iRowSeq
    An interface that defines methods implemented by row sequence implementations that represent a row of data in storage.
    iRowSeq.Iterator
    An interface for an iterator that all row sequences must implement.
    MutableDataPoint
    A mutable DataPoint that stores a value and a timestamp.
    Query
    A query to retrieve data from the TSDB.
    RateOptions
    Provides additional options that will be used when calculating rates.
    SeekableView
    Provides a zero-copy view to iterate through data points.
    SimpleHistogram
    A simple bucketed histogram with a fixed number of buckets, an underflow counter and an overflow counter.
    SimpleHistogramDataPointAdapter
    An adapter of TSDB's HistogramDataPoint interface with Yamas's Histogram interface.
    Span
    Represents a read-only sequence of continuous data points.
    TSDB
    Thread-safe implementation of the TSDB client.
    TSDB.OperationMode
    The operation mode (role) of the TSD.
    TSQuery
    Parameters and state to query the underlying storage system for timeseries data points.
    TSSubQuery
    Represents the parameters for an individual sub query on a metric or specific timeseries.
    WritableDataPoints
    Represents a mutable sequence of continuous data points.
    WriteableDataPointFilterPlugin
    A filter that can determine whether or not time series should be allowed assignment based on their metric and tags.
